  <discussion>Species 3 (1 in the flora):</discussion>
  <discussion>Chenia includes both cleistocarpous and peristomate taxa.  The diagnostic characters are leaves ligulate to spathulate, sharply crenulate to irregularly dentate above with sharp mid-marginal wall projections, often sharply apiculate by a distinctive thick-walled cell or cells, distal laminal cells large, weakly trigonous, epapillose, and red in KOH solution.</discussion>
